You do not use `this`in Vue templates.  Every variable in a Vue template has an implicit `this`.

```
&lt;h v-html=&quot;&#39;Items (&#39; + dataArray.length + &#39;)&#39;&quot;&gt;&lt;/h&gt;
```

```
&lt;h v-html=&quot;`Items (${dataArray.length})`&quot;&gt;&lt;/h&gt;
```

If dataArray is null or undefined at mount, use a v-if.
```
&lt;h v-if=&#39;dataArray&#39; v-html=&quot;&#39;Items (&#39; + dataArray.length + &#39;)&#39;&quot;&gt;&lt;/h&gt;
&lt;div v-else&gt;Loading...&lt;/div&gt;
```

As have been mentioned before there is no need to use **`this`** in template syntax to get the values of reactive data (properties).

Another way to do this using a **`computed property`** that would return the `length` of the table data at any point. And use that in the template.

**At Script:**

    &lt;script&gt;
    export default {
      data() {
        return {
          dataArray: [
            {
              itemId: 0,
              itemName: &quot;some name 1&quot;
            },
            {
              itemId: 1,
              itemName: &quot;some name 2&quot;
            }
          ]
        };
      },
      computed: {
        tableLength: function() {
          return this.dataArray.length;
        }
      }
    };
    &lt;/script&gt;

**At Template:**

    &lt;h v-if=&#39;dataArray&#39;&gt;Items {{tableLength}}&lt;/h&gt;

OR

    &lt;h v-if=&quot;dataArray&quot; v-html=&quot;&#39;Items &#39; + tableLength&quot;&gt;&lt;/h&gt;

